Description: Mint condition, like new custom-made to order Left-handed Eastwood Wandre’ Tri-Lam semi-hollow Body guitar. Collector’s item. Only a few were made, and this one is super rare because it was a special order. no scratches, not breaks, no cracks. Like new. Includes original premiere hardshell case. The original 1960’s version goes for $3300! The mini-humbucker pick up sounds amazing , and you can hear the guitar very well unplugged. In early 1960’s Europe, the Tri-Lam was one of Wandrè’s best-selling models. As all 60’s Wandre models, the original version had an aluminum neck. This modern version sports a set maple neck, suspended pickguard, pickup and master volume, and a full hollowbody design that includes the unusually stylish grilled f-holes.
